 N/A 1.00 1.00", "bbox": [122.8, 380.6, 678.6, 388.1]}, {"text": "35_5_40_200k 0.96 0.89 0.99 0.99", "bbox": [124.9, 393.9, 678.6, 401.5]}, {"text": "35_10_20_200k 0.96 0.93 1.00 1.00", "bbox": [122.8, 407.1, 678.6, 414.7]}, {"text": "35_10_40_200k 0.93 0.79 0.96 0.96", "bbox": [122.8, 420.4, 678.6, 427.9]}, {"text": "40_10_10_100k 0.81 N/A 0.85 0.87", "bbox": [122.8, 433.6, 678.6, 441.2]}, {"text": "40_10_10_200k 0.73 N/A 0.90 0.90", "bbox": [122.8, 446.8, 678.6, 454.4]}, {"text": "40_20_10_100k 0.61 N/A 0.71 0.69", "bbox": [122.8, 460.2, 678.6, 467.7]}, {"text": "40_20_10_200k 0.60 N/A 0.69 0.67", "bbox": [122.8, 473.4, 678.6, 481.0]}, {"text": "40_10_20_100k 1.00 0.90 1.00 1.00", "bbox": [122.8, 486.6, 678.6, 494.2]}, {"text": "40_10_20_200k 1.00 0.93 1.00 1.00", "bbox": [122.8, 499.9, 678.6, 507.5]}, {"text": "40_10_25_100k 0.94 0.94 1.00 1.00", "bbox": [122.8, 513.1, 678.6, 520.7]}, {"text": "40_20_30_100k 0.95 0.92 1.00 1.00", "bbox": [122.8, 526.4, 678.6, 534.0]}, {"text": "40_10_25_200k 0.96 0.94 0.99 0.99", "bbox": [122.8, 539.7, 678.6, 547.3]}, {"text": "50_10_10_100k 0.78 N/A 0.88 0.88", "bbox": [122.8, 552.9, 678.6, 560.5]}, {"text": "50_10_10_200k 0.80 N/A 0.89 0.88", "bbox": [122.8, 566.2, 678.6, 573.7]}, {"text": "50_20_10_100k 0.63 N/A 0.73 0.71", "bbox": [122.8, 579.4, 678.6, 587.0]}, {"text": "50_20_10_200k 0.63 N/A 0.71 0.72", "bbox": [122.8, 592.7, 678.6, 600.3]}, {"text": "50_10_30_100k 0.96 0.94 1.00 1.00", "bbox": [122.8, 606.0, 678.6, 613.5]}, {"text": "50_20_20_200k 0.97 N/A 0.98 0.98", "bbox": [122.8, 619.2, 678.6, 626.8]}, {"text": "50_20_30_200k 0.95 N/A 1.00 1.00", "bbox": [122.8, 632.5, 678.6, 640.0]}, {"text": "Stem Cell 0.98 0.41 0.98 0.91", "bbox": [132.9, 645.7, 678.6, 653.3]}, {"text": "(6 dimensions, 5 subpopulations)", "bbox": [90.3, 659.0, 209.7, 666.6]}, {"text": "NDD 0.8 0.77 0.79 0.8", "bbox": [141.8, 672.3, 676.6, 679.8]}, {"text": "(12 dimensions, 8 subpopulations)", "bbox": [88.2, 685.5, 211.7, 693.1]}, {"text": "CyTOF 0.59 0.53 0.84 0.82", "bbox": [137.6, 698.7, 678.6, 706.3]}, {"text": "(39 dimensions, 24 subpopulations)", "bbox": [86.1, 712.1, 213.9, 719.6]}, {"text": "F-measure is calculated using the original hand-gate labels and the estimated labels generated by each analysis method. The true-positives are found if the", "bbox": [45.5, 733.7, 724.4, 743.8]}, {"text": "methods assign the same labels to points belonging to the same subpopulation in the hand-gated data. The more true-positives found, the higher the F-", "bbox": [45.5, 748.9, 706.3, 759.0]}, {"text": "measure, which ranges from 0 to 1, with 1 being the highest. Partition-based methods perform consistently well on data ranging from 5 to 50 dimensions. In", "bbox": [45.5, 764.1, 722.3, 774.2]}, {"text": "the simulations, d-PAC and b-PAC perform just as well or better than flowMeans and SPADE. flowMeans gives drastically different F-measures for the", "bbox": [45.5, 779.2, 702.2, 789.3]}, {"text": "cases 20_10_40_100k and 20_20_40_100k: 0.25386 vs. 0.92518; this large difference is likely due to the random initiation of cluster centers. In the hand-", "bbox": [45.5, 794.3, 716.7, 804.4]}, {"text": "gated datasets, SPADE has the worst performance. Ultimately, the performance of flowMeans and SPADE deteriorate for the 39-dimensional real CyTOF", "bbox": [45.5, 809.5, 717.8, 819.6]}, {"text": "data, while d-PAC and b-PAC perform consistently well.", "bbox": [45.5, 824.6, 289.8, 834.7]}, {"text": "In this table, simulated data have the following convention: a_b_c_d, where a denotes the number of dimensions/markers, b denotes the number of", "bbox": [45.5, 839.8, 687.3, 849.9]}, {"text": "subpopulations, c denotes the edge size of the hypercube for data generation, and d denotes the number of cells. The clustering problem becomes harder", "bbox": [45.5, 855.0, 717.5, 865.1]}, {"text": "as the number of subpopulations increases and the data space volume decreases. We report the results for simulated cases that worked for all methods,", "bbox": [45.5, 870.1, 712.1, 880.2]}, {"text": "except for higher-dimension cases in which the clusters are nearby and SPADE failed to cluster; these SPADE results are denoted with N/A.", "bbox": [45.5, 885.3, 657.4, 895.4]}, {"text": "** In this table, 1.00 means a number which rounds up to 1.00.", "bbox": [45.5, 900.4, 317.0, 910.5]}, {"text": "https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pcbi.1005875.t001", "bbox": [45.5, 920.3, 233.3, 930.9]}, {"text": "PLOS Computational Biology | https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pcbi.1005875 December 27, 2017 10 / 37", "bbox": [45.5, 946.7, 727.3, 956.8]}]}